AGI - At least 5 rockets were launched from northern Iraq to a base of the international anti-Isis coalition in nearby Syria: they announced the Iraqi security forces that found the vehicle used to make launches. A "existing research and inspection" was launched in the province of Ninive to find the authors of the operation, said in a note Iraqi security forces.
&nbsp;
This is the first major attack against the coalition troops led by Washington, after several weeks of calm: this winter, the pro-Iranian armed factions carried out dozens of missile and drone attacks against American soldiers in the Middle East.
&nbsp;
The attack on the U.S. military base in Syria on Saturday evening "is only the beginning," said the philian Shiite formation in Iraq, Kataib Hezbollah, in what appears as a claim of what happened. The Israeli newspaper Times of Israel reports it. The resumption of the attacks against U.S. forces in Syria and Iraq would be related to the failure of the U.S. troops from Iraq that the Prime Minister of Baghdad Al Sudani did not get on the occasion of a recent visit to Washington.

