Machado has been banned by public offices for 15 years by the courts loyal to the Maduro government. The accused - fasulla according to the same Machado - is that of corruption. Machado tried to present a wooden head with the aim of continuing to fight on the side and eventually running, but the electoral authorities also blocked that candidate. Another last-minute candidate, Manuel Rosales>, governor of the oil-rich state of Zulia, whose party is a member of the opposition alliance, retired from the race.
&nbsp;
Many countries, including the United States, refused to accept the results of the 2018 Maduro victory, leading fraud and lack of transparency. That vote was boycotted by the opposition. The United Nations estimates that almost eight million Venezuelans have fled their country since 2014, the year after the settlement of Maduro. In the last ten years there has been a serious economic crisis marked by galloping inflation and the shortage of food and medicines, which have thrown the population into misery.&nbsp;
