AGI - In Spain, vote in the Basque Country: Regional elections which, according to the polls, will be won by the heirs of the Eta> political arm, which could force the socialists of Premier Pedro Sanchez to have to choose between two allies. The polls for the first time assigned a victory to the left independent coalition EH Bildu>, whose hegemonic formation, Sortu>, is the heir of Eta's political emanation, the organization founded in 1958 that killed more than 850 people for more than forty years until he abandoned the armed struggle in 2011. Strong of a great popularity among young people thanks to left-wing positions on economic and social issues and having softened his speech on independence, EH Bildu could overcome the Basque Nationalist Party > (PNV, centrist), which has continuously ruled the region over the last 44 years, except for a short break of three years.
&nbsp;
There is no big difference in votes between PNV and EH Bildu, which would leave socialists as a need for the balance. But at the national level, Pedro Sanchez's government is supported by the decisive support of a network of regional allies, including PNV and EH Bildu. Analysts believe that regional tensions will not reflect on the stability of the national government. So far the PNV has ruled the Basque countries in coalition with the socialists, whose regional leader has already excluded from supporting Bildu; and Pedro Sanchez's debt to EH Bildu for helping him to rule could be welded by giving the party the office of mayor of the city of Pamplona, capital of Navarre, a neighboring region that the Independents consider part of the historical territory of the Basque Countries.
&nbsp;
Some 1.8 million voters are called to vote on a total population of 2.2 million, which will elect the 75 MPs of the Basque Parliament. Electoral seats opened at 09:00 local time and will close at 20:00. The Basque Country has, after Madrid, the highest per capita income in Spain, with an average of almost 36,000 euros per year per inhabitant. According to Caixabank Research data, the region contributes 5.9% to Spanish GDP (the region that contributes more, the region of Madrid, contributes 19.4%). It is also the region with the lowest unemployment rate of the country (7.9%), according to the data of the Basque government.&nbsp;
